testdbname.pipeline_errors.execution_id: ​​A unique ID that represents the data pipeline run. Each invocation of a data pipeline run has a unique execution_id.
testdbname.pipeline_errors.execution_time: The time the error occurred (utc) example: 2021-06-17T08:42:19.165+0000.
testdbname.pipeline_errors.job_type: The type of job that produced failing rows (eg BATCH).
testdbname.pipeline_errors.row: The row that didn’t match the expected output for that row.
testdbname.pipeline_errors.transform: The name of the pipeline and node that failed formatted like “<pipeline_name>.<node_name>”.
